cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on physical layer authentication in machine-type communication networks.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is also likely as the paper discusses security impacts of the proposed protocol.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper utilizes likelihood-ratio testing and channel-state information.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper develops a queueing model to capture delay impacts.
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is less likely but still possible as the paper mentions use cases with low latency requirements.
